    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Phonograph records played at 78 revolutions-per-minute, the standard playing speed for records until the mid-20th century. The maximum length of play per side was 4 1/2 minutes, and they appeared most commonly in ten-inch and twelve-inch formats.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
